Say & Do
Pain

-Is a sports package worth the price?
-Sports are a part of my life but I won’t go out of my way to
watch them.
-There are a few teams/events I’m willing to watch at all.
-I won’t pay for a sports package if the cost doesn’t give me what I want.
-I need the ability to opt-in or out of a service. Flexibility is important to me.
-I want to be able to watch the sports I want but not if it interferes with more
important parts of my life.
-Watching sports can be too much of an investment if I have trouble accessing
and paying for a service.
-If I don’t have to go out of my way to watch the sport/event, I’m happy and
content.
-TV channel guide or streaming service guide
-Background distractions taking attention away from the game
-Brief Google search for free streaming links
-Broken links that don’t work
-Many advertisements
-Buffering and low quality free streams
-Comes home from work and puts on a game/event
-Performs other activity while game is on in the background
-Tunes into game with full attention sporadically
-Searches briefly for free options for games that are not on
national television**
-Have favorite sports channels at your fingertips
-Learn what you absolutely need in a sports package
-It would be great to have a sports package that wasn’t so
expensive
-Single game purchases for games would be nice
-I want to get rid of cable but I like some of the sports-
channels I have
-I can’t watch my hometown team without breaking the bank.
-It’s just not worth it.
-Not having the ability to watch regional sports / favorite team
in another location
-Sports packages and cable are too expensive
-Too many advertisements on free links online and it’s too
sketchy
-Not enough time to look for event if it’s not on tv or only uses
streaming service
